"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-04-Zhang-hopes-his-Olympic-silver-can-boost-popularity-of-tennis-in-China-1vMUG59wtWg-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Sports Scene  Copied  Zhang Zhizhen and Wang Xinyu won China's first mixed doubles tennis silver medal at the 2024 Paris Summer Olympics on Friday. CGTN Sports Scene's Greg Laffradi caught up with Zhang at the airport for a quick interview.  Zhang was scheduled to pair with Zheng Qinwen in the mixed doubles event at the Paris Games, but Wang was asked to replace Zheng at the last minute. Although the pair did not have much time to get familiar with each other, they did unexpectedly well as partners at Roland Garros.  Zhang, Wang and Zheng are three of the top talents among the rising generation of tennis players in China. Zhang said he hopes their performances in the French capital can help increase the sport's popularity in the country, because the more children play tennis, the better its development will be.  Zhang also became a father for the first time during the Paris Olympics. According to his wife, their daughter name is \\\"Aoyun,\\\" which means \\\"Olympic.\\\" Zhang said in the interview that he felt sorry he could not be there with his wife during the delivery. His wife has already posted a request on Sina Weibo for him to hurry back home and help change diapers.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"